<BR>
<B>Director - Harold C. Petzold Jr., Esq. (WFA Certified, NYS Licensed Guide #5098, Leave No Trace - Master Educator)</B>
<BR>
<BR>
Harold Petzold  is the Director of Outdoor Activities. Harold has worked with youth and adults 
in a variety of capacities.  He was the first approved hike leader for the Chapter Youth Program for the 
New York - Northern New Jersey Chapter of the Appalachian Mountain Club (AMC) and has planned family 
hikes with the Berkshire Chapter of the AMC. For the past several years he has provided Adult 
hikes and teaches outdoor navigation as part of the community education programs for Wayne 
Township and the Village of Ridgewood. A licensed New York State Outdoor Guide and Leave No Trace 
Master Educator, Harold brings 40 years hiking and camping experience to our program.
